Liana Petersen, one of two women shot dead in Melville on New Year’s Day, is being laid to rest in Hanover Park, Cape Town. The 41-year-old was out celebrating with her 11-year-old daughter at the popular Poppy’s restaurant in Johannesburg when she was caught in a drive-by shooting. eNCA's Ronald Masinda has the details. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - A mother, who was a retail estate professional, has been laid to rest at her home town in Cape Town. She was one of the two women shot dead in the Melville drive-by-shooting on New Year's Day. READ: Cape Town family wants answers after Melville shooting Liana Peterson had relocated to Johannesburg with her daughter due to work opportunities. Peterson is being celebrated as a go-getter.